A '''door tenant''' is a [[barrister]] who has been granted permission to join a set of [[chambers (law)|chambers]] and work with them from premises outside the chambers themselves.<ref name="williams">Anna Williams (ed), ''Chambers Student Guide to the Legal Profession'' (London: Chambers and Partners, 2007) {{ISBN|0-85514-310-X}}</ref> Those members who work on the premises are simply 'tenants' while 'squatters' are those who make legitimate use of the premises without belonging to the set.<ref name="williams"/>

